@Node "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction:@{uu}@{ub}

Use GetInfo to get some useful information about files (size, protection bits,
date, comment, type, etc.).


@Endnode
@Node "System requirements"

@{b}@{u}System requirements:@{uu}@{ub}

GetInfo requires:

   - Kickstart 2.04+
   - asl.library (if you want to make use of a file requester)
   - whatis.library (included in the archive)


@Endnode
@Node "Installation"

@{b}@{u}Installation:@{uu}@{ub}

Just drag the GetInfo icon anywhere you want.


@Endnode
@Node "Usage"

@{b}@{u}Usage:@{uu}@{ub}

GetInfo can be started from Workbench by double-clicking its icon. Then a file
requester appears.
Otherwise you can start the program from a Shell window with the following
form:

   GetInfo [<file>]

where <file> must be a valid file name (if not specified, a file requester
appears).
After you select a file name, a requester like the following pops up:

   +--------------------------------+
   |GetInfo                         |
   +--------------------------------+
   | File name: Clock               |
   | Size: 13876                    |
   | Blocks: 28                     |
   | Protection: ---ARWED           |
   | Date: 02-09-92                 |
   | Time: 12:25:14                 |
   | Comment:                       |
   | Type: Exe                      |
   +--------------------------------+
   |  +------+            +------+  |
   |  | Next |            | Quit |  |
   |  +------+            +------+  |
   +--------------------------------+

Click on the Next button (not available if you specified a file name in the
command line) to select another file through the file requester. Click on the
Quit button to quit the program.


@Endnode
